9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 396, L.D. 628, “An Act Regarding
10 Eligibility to Apply for a Department of Education Diploma”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §257-A, sub-§1-A, as amended by PL 2023, c. 171, §1, is
14 further amended to read:
15 1-A. Eligibility for students impacted by COVID-19 pandemic. Notwithstanding
16 the eligibility requirements in subsection 1, a student is eligible to apply for a Department
17 of Education diploma if that student is a 4th year secondary school student and is unable to
18 satisfy the requirements for a diploma from a school administrative unit because the student
19 experienced a significant interruption to the student's education as a result of the COVID‑19
20 pandemic and civil emergency during the student's secondary school education history.
21 This subsection is repealed on September 1, 2026.
22 Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §257-A, sub-§1-C is enacted to read:
23 1-C. Exception for disruption to student's education conditions. A student is
24 eligible to apply for a Department of Education diploma if that student is at least a 4th year
25 secondary school student and is unable to satisfy the requirements for a diploma from a
26 school administrative unit because of a disruption to the student's education during the
27 student's secondary school education history. A disruption to the student's education may
28 include, but is not limited to, conditions described in section 5161, subsection 2-A.
29 Sec. 3. 20-A MRSA §5161, sub-§2-A, as amended by PL 2021, c. 445, §3, is
30 further amended to read:
31 2-A. Education disruption. "Education disruption" means disruption of the
32 educational program of an elementary or secondary school student as a result of:
33 A. Homelessness or, foster care placement or another housing disruption;
